1 than fifty percent (50%) of its annual operating budget on
2 instructional expenditures.
3 B. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
4 its annual operating budget on instructional expenditures, it shall
5 increase its instructional expenditures by no less than two percent
6 (2%) each year until the amount spent on instructional expenditures
7 reaches fifty percent (50%) of its annual operating budget.
8 C. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
9 its annual operating budget on instructional expenditures and does
10 not increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this
11 section, the school district shall receive a written warning notice
12 from the State Department of Education. The notice shall also be
13 posted on the website of the school district.
14 D. If a school district spends less than fifty percent (50%) of
15 its annual operating budget on instructional expenditures and does
16 not increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this
17 section for four (4) consecutive years after receiving the notice
18 provided in subsection C of this section, the school district shall
19 increase compensation for all teachers in the school district by two
20 percent (2%) for each year in that period in which the school
21 district did not increase instructional expenditures by a minimum of
22 two percent (2%). The pay increase required pursuant to this
23 subsection shall be permanent.
24 E. As used in this section:
